dc:description: Fine pale buff clay with worn brown glaze. Nozzle with triangular termination which is partly broken. Volutes at base do not encroach on rim. small slit shaped air hole in neck. Grooved rim. On discus two short swords alternate with two pairs of crossed greaves. No handle. Base ring set off by grooves. Part of discus and left side broken.
